# ========================================
# Database Configuration
# ========================================

# POSTGRES_URL
# ------------
# Leave this UNSET for local development - it will automatically use DuckDB
# The app will use data/spotify.duckdb which is fast and doesn't count against Vercel quotas
#
# Only set POSTGRES_URL if you want to test with Postgres locally:
# POSTGRES_URL=postgres://user:password@localhost:5432/spotify
#
# For Vercel production, set this in your Vercel project settings (not in this file)

# ========================================
# Spotify API Credentials (Optional)
# ========================================

# Required only if you want to run enrichment scripts (enrich_metadata.py)
# Get these from: https://developer.spotify.com/dashboard
#
# SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here
# SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret_here

# ========================================
# How It Works
# ========================================
#
# Local Development:
#   - No POSTGRES_URL → Uses DuckDB (data/spotify.duckdb)
#   - Fast queries, no network latency, free
#
# Production (Vercel):
#   - POSTGRES_URL set in Vercel dashboard → Uses Vercel Postgres
#   - Serverless-compatible, globally distributed
